  abstract  = {Gibson's foundational work revolutionizes perception theory by proposing that organisms directly perceive affordances in their environment without the need for cognitive mediation. This ecological approach shifts focus from information processing models to direct pickup of environmental information, emphasizing the relationship between organism and environment. The concept of affordances—action possibilities directly perceived in the environment—has influenced fields from psychology to HCI design. Gibson argues that perception is not about constructing internal representations but about detecting invariants in the ambient optic array that specify opportunities for action.}
